com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.iterators

Class FilteredIterator<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.util.collections.iterators.FilteredIterator<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of elements returned by this iterator at each iteration.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<E>

    @NotThreadSafe
public class FilteredIterator<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<E>
    The FilteredIterator class is used to iterate over a collection where certain values are skipped. The values to skip are determined by a Filter instance, where values rejected by the filter (Filter.filter(value) = false) are skipped.

    This class is not thread safe, even if the underlying iterator is. Specifically, invalid behavior from the next() and hasNext() methods may be observed if more than one thread are accessing this iterator concurrently.
